e Federal Property and Administrative Services Act of 1949 (ch. 288, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/380"},"text":"63 Stat. 380","children":[],"tail":"), which is restated as section 303(c) [303(b)] of the revised title. The words “United States Postal Service” are substituted for “Postmaster General” because of section 6("},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"o","children":[],"tail":") of the Postal Reorganization Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/375"},"text":"Public Law 91–375","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/783"},"text":"84 Stat. 783","children":[],"tail":"). The words “real, personal, or other” are omitted as unnecessary."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
